reviews.text: Finally, I got to have this carrot cake after coming twice and was told already closed! The carrot cake is soft, fresh with a good amount of eggs. Saw many people having the black one, and I will be back to try the black one soon!

Lovely carrot cake,
Well fried , heaps of eggs and cai poh

Best wishes to the chefs and great year ahead !
From a happy diner

I actually had trouble finding the stall as there are a couple of coffeeshops at block 150A üòÇ. So for easier reference, they are located opposite the Yang Ming seafood.
Am very happy to see younger owners at the stall, and very polite and overall service level is very good. They even have preorder options and you can call to place the orders.
Food wise, the black carrot cake was good and not overly sweet which I read from other reviews. It is good and will come back for their carrot cake again. Keep up the good work!

I had a wonderful plate of the black carrot cake, served piping hot. The carrot cake was on the sweeter note side (the way I like them), it was moist and every piece was well coated with the dark sauce. I had the $4 plate, and it was a good-sized portion - definitely filled my tummy with yummilious carrot cake and egg.

There was also a good balance of umami and Wok Hey to the dish, well worth the calories and indulgence. And the travel all the way from Tampines to Bishan!

Owned by a young couple, with great positive attitude and naturally, the food was cooked with passion. The stall was also kept thoroughly clean. Hope more Customers will support this couple in their business venture!  :)
